{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_43","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc 'nl -ba ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_rollback.feature'","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Run Rollback\n     2\t  A paused or failed run can be rewound to a durable stage boundary using a\n     3\t  persisted rollback point. Logical rollback updates canonical run state first;\n     4\t  hard rollback then attempts to reset the repository to the recorded git SHA.\n     5\t\n     6\t  # SC-ROLLBACK-001\n     7\t  Scenario: Soft rollback rewinds to a visible checkpoint\n     8\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"rb-alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n     9\t    And project \"rb-alpha\" is selected as active\n    10\t    And the project has visible rollback points for \"planning\" and \"implementation\"\n    11\t    And the current run snapshot status is \"failed\"\n    12\t    When the user runs \"run rollback --to planning\"\n    13\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    14\t    And run.json is restored to the planning rollback snapshot\n    15\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"paused\" with no active run\n    16\t    And the journal ends with a \"rollback_performed\" event for \"planning\"\n    17\t\n    18\t  # SC-ROLLBACK-002\n    19\t  Scenario: Hard rollback resets canonical state before the repository\n    20\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"rb-bravo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    21\t    And project \"rb-bravo\" is selected as active\n    22\t    And the target rollback point for \"implementation\" records a git SHA\n    23\t    And the current run snapshot status is \"paused\"\n    24\t    When the user runs \"run rollback --to implementation --hard\"\n    25\t    Then the logical rollback is committed before the git reset is attempted\n    26\t    And the repository reset targets the git SHA stored in the rollback point\n    27\t\n    28\t  # SC-ROLLBACK-003\n    29\t  Scenario: Rollback rejects non-resumable run statuses\n    30\t    Given initialized workspace projects with snapshots in statuses \"not_started\", \"running\", and \"completed\"\n    31\t    When the user runs \"run rollback --to planning\" for each project\n    32\t    Then each command fails with a clear rollback-status error\n    33\t    And none of the commands mutate run.json\n    34\t\n    35\t  # SC-ROLLBACK-004\n    36\t  Scenario: Rollback rejects a stage outside the project flow\n    37\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"rb-charlie\" using flow \"standard\"\n    38\t    And project \"rb-charlie\" is selected as active\n    39\t    And the current run snapshot status is \"failed\"\n    40\t    When the user runs \"run rollback --to ci_plan\"\n    41\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"not part of flow\"\n    42\t\n    43\t  # SC-ROLLBACK-005\n    44\t  Scenario: Rollback rejects a stage with no visible checkpoint\n    45\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"rb-delta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    46\t    And project \"rb-delta\" is selected as active\n    47\t    And the current run snapshot status is \"paused\"\n    48\t    And no visible rollback point exists for \"review\"\n    49\t    When the user runs \"run rollback --to review\"\n    50\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"no persisted rollback point exists\"\n    51\t\n    52\t  # SC-ROLLBACK-006\n    53\t  Scenario: Multiple sequential rollbacks keep rollback metadata monotonic\n    54\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"rb-echo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    55\t    And project \"rb-echo\" is selected as active\n    56\t    And the current run has visible rollback points for \"planning\", \"implementation\", and \"qa\"\n    57\t    When the user rolls back to \"implementation\" and then to \"planning\"\n    58\t    Then rollback_point_meta.rollback_count increases on each rollback\n    59\t    And rollback_point_meta.last_rollback_id matches the most recent rollback point\n    60\t    And run history excludes the abandoned branch after each rollback\n    61\t\n    62\t  # SC-ROLLBACK-007\n    63\t  Scenario: Resume after rollback continues from the restored boundary\n    64\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"rb-foxtrot\" using flow \"standard\"\n    65\t    And project \"rb-foxtrot\" is selected as active\n    66\t    And the project has a rollback point at \"planning\" whose snapshot resumes at \"implementation\"\n    67\t    When the user runs \"run rollback --to planning\" and then \"run resume\"\n    68\t    Then the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n    69\t    And the first resumed stage is \"implementation\"\n    70\t    And the rolled-back implementation history from the abandoned branch remains hidden\n    71\t\n    72\t  # SC-ROLLBACK-008\n    73\t  Scenario: Hard rollback failure preserves the logical rollback\n    74\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"rb-golf\" using flow \"standard\"\n    75\t    And project \"rb-golf\" is selected as active\n    76\t    And the current run snapshot status is \"failed\"\n    77\t    And the target rollback point for \"implementation\" records a git SHA\n    78\t    And the repository reset will fail\n    79\t    When the user runs \"run rollback --to implementation --hard\"\n    80\t    Then the command fails with a git-reset error\n    81\t    And run.json remains in the logically rolled-back paused state\n    82\t    And the journal still contains the \"rollback_performed\" event\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
